[Dothan, with a population of 65 496 as of the 2010 census, is a city in Dale, Henry, and Houston counties in the U.S. state of Alabama; located in the state's southeastern corner, approximately 20 miles (32 km) west of the Georgia state line and 16 miles (26 km) north of Florida, it is the county seat of Houston County (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dothan,_Alabama).

ProMED-mail has posted several reports of community outbreaks of tuberculosis in the past, for example, in Singapore (Tuberculosis, MDR - Singapore: (AMK) neighborhood outbreak, RFI 20160618.4294856) and in Shanghai (Tuberculosis, MDR - China: (Shanghai) primary, neighborhood outbreaks, 2009-2012 20161216.4702532).

Transmission of tuberculosis usually requires close, repeated or prolonged contact with a contagious individual in a poorly ventilated environment, which occurs in households or institutions, such as homeless shelters. However, in Singapore, a neighborhood outbreak extended over a 4-year period, linked to a 2012 outbreak of multidrug resistant tuberculosis (MDR) TB that involved 6 cases of MDR TB, 5 of whom frequented 3 cybercafes at a shopping mall; the 6th case was a family member. All 6 individuals had isolates of _Mycobacterium tuberculosis_ with a matching genotype.

The MDR TB outbreak in Shanghai was similar to that in Singapore in that most cases with matching genotypes did not have anything in common other than living in the same neighborhood or using the same public facilities such as food markets. Only a small number of cases were traced to household contacts.

The news report above of the tuberculosis outbreak in Dothan, says that multiple cases of tuberculosis in Dothan over the past 2 years are linked to several downtown nightclubs; however, the news report fails to give details, such as the number of cases, their ages or any other characteristic, whether the isolates of _M. tuberculosis_ were MDR, and whether the isolates were genetically linked. More information on this outbreak would be appreciated from knowledgeable sources. - Mod.ML

HealthMap: Alabama, United States: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5650233,205]
